   <item>
    <widget class="QGroupBox" name="groupBox_autoexpand">
     <property name="title">
      <string>Auto-expand to gap</string>
     </property>
     <layout class="QFormLayout" name="formLayout_autoexpand">
      <item row="0" column="0">
       <widget class="QCheckBox" name="kcfg_autoExpandOnEdgeDrag">
        <property name="text">
         <string>Snap to screen edge and fill available space when dropping a window near one</string>
        </property>
        <property name="toolTip">
         <string>Windows-Snap style: drag a window by its titlebar and drop it with the cursor against a screen edge - it fills the largest reachable free area containing the window (top edge extends down, corner fills the quadrant); on an otherwise-empty screen it takes the half toward that edge. A shadowed preview shows the result while you hold near the edge. Applies only to native mouse drags - a normal grid-overlay placement commits exactly the size you selected (use Meta+Alt+E there for an explicit fill). Off by default - you'll also want to disable KWin's built-in ElectricBorder snap so the two don't both fire on the same edge. (Ignored while "auto-trigger on drag" is on - that picker owns the drag instead.)</string>
        </property>
       </widget>
      </item>
     </layout>
    </widget>
   </item>
   <item>
    <widget class="QGroupBox" name="groupBox_monitors">
     <property name="title">
      <string>Per-monitor grid overrides</string>
     </property>
     <layout class="QVBoxLayout" name="verticalLayout_monitors">
      <item>
       <widget class="QLabel" name="label_monitorsHint">
        <property name="text">
         <string>One monitor per line, as &lt;b&gt;name = columns x rows&lt;/b&gt; — for example:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DP-2 = 8x6&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;tt&gt;HDMI-A-1 = 2x6&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Names must match &lt;b&gt;System Settings → Display Configuration&lt;/b&gt; exactly. Lines starting with # are ignored. Leave empty to use the default grid above on every monitor. (The older JSON format still works if you already have one saved.)</string>
        </property>
        <property name="wordWrap">
         <bool>true</bool>
        </property>
       </widget>
      </item>
      <item>
